    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1024" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀνί̄η</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ης</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">torment, vexation;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄνευθε πόνου καὶ ἀνίης</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 7.192</span></i>; of Scylla (abstr. for concr.),
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">bane</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 12.233</span></i>;
          and so of persons, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δαιτὸς ἀνί̄η</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 17.446</span></i> (cf. 377); <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀνί̄η καὶ πολὺς ὕπνος</span>, an ‘infliction,’
          ‘weariness to the flesh,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 15.394</span></i>,
          cf. <i><span class="en">Od. 20.52</span></i>. Cf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀνῑάζω</span>. (Od.)</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
